Source: World Health Organization (WHO), CSR, Disease Outbreak News, Tue 11
May 2004 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2004_05_11/en/>


Yellow fever in Burkina Faso
----------------------------------
As of Mon 10 May 2004, the Ministry of Health, Burkina Faso, has reported a
total of 25 suspect cases of yellow fever in the districts of
Bobo-Dioulasso and Gaoua. Of the 16 samples collected, 4 were
laboratory-confirmed by the WHO Collaborating Centre for Yellow Fever at
the Institut Pasteur, Dakar, Senegal. The 4 confirmed cases were from
Bobo-Dioulasso.

WHO is working with the Ministry of Health's Crisis Committee to determine
the most appropriate strategies for disease control. A MOH/WHO team is
currently conducting further epidemiological investigations in the field.

